  <title translate="true">Forces</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">&apos;Forces&apos;</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is the collective term we use for kinematic-force calculations and display.</text></para>
          <list id="14" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Force at Pin-Joints and Slide-Joints </text></li>
          </list>
          <list id="15" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Drive Torque</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Drive Force</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Cam Contact Force</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Spring Force</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">Kinetostatic Forces</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> are those forces and reaction forces in parts and at joints that are a consequence of their movement.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">We tend to use the terms:</text></para>
          <list id="11" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">&apos;Drive Torque&apos;</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> for the &apos;moment&apos; a Rotary Motor must provide to the mechanism</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">&apos;Drive Force&apos;</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> for the &apos;linear force&apos; a Linear Motor must provide to the mechanism</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
